description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for a better work/life balance?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hampshire Hospitals are currently offering a range of shifts to suit you including: weekdays only, weekends only, early, late, long day, twilight night or clinic hours (perhaps to fit around the school day).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer our dedicated, motivated and invaluable team of Bank Nurses the following benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support with Revalidation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid Trust Induction, Mandatory training and development opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set working days – flexible to suit you&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Choice of Hospital Site– Basingstoke, Winchester or Andover&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Weekly Pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS Pension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Variety of work available in all clinical areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In addition, we can also offer you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- A supportive and friendly environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- All wards are led by a Clinical Matron with an experienced team of professionals helping each other to meet their full potential while providing high quality and compassionate care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held at a time and venue (Winchester or Basingstoke) to suit you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to have a chat about the available opportunities or to arrange an informal visit please contact Nina Oldham on 01256 319875 nina.oldham@hhft.nhs.uk or Janice Johnson 01256 313374 janice.johnson@hhft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
